Joseph Olaoluwa Page Financials has said it emerged the winner of the ‘Consumer Credit Brand of the Year 2020 Award’ and the ‘Most Innovative Consumer Lender of the Year 2020 Award’ at the BusinessDay Banks And other Financial Institutions Awards 2020. This is the second consecutive year the organisation will win the awards, according to a statement on Thursday. The Chairman of Page Financials, Dr Adewale Olawoyin, said, “Successes like these, particularly in the areas of innovation and branding, speak volumes to what we characterise as the PAGE WAY – a way that puts customer experience above all – while deploying 21st-century business tools driven by technology.” Receiving the awards on behalf of the board and management, the Chief Executive Officer, Mr Segun Akintemi, said, “This is truly excellent news and a testament to the unreserved support and co-operation we have received from our customers, furthermore, reflecting the effectiveness of our board and management’s strategic thinking and direction. “We are encouraged to do more for our customers, as we continue to provide loans and manage investments, across multiple platforms to Nigerians in a responsive and innovative way.” Copyright PUNCH.
